

A multi-location coffee chain is generating consistent transactional data but lacks visibility into the structural drivers of its revenue performance.

While raw sales records exist, management cannot clearly determine:

What factors primarily drive revenue growth — product mix, timing, or location?

Whether sales performance is evenly distributed or heavily concentrated.

When customer demand peaks and declines throughout the week.

Which operational adjustments could improve efficiency and profitability.

How store-level performance compares across locations.

Without structured analysis, decision-making remains reactive and assumption-based rather than data-driven.

This project aims to transform six months of transactional sales data into a strategic business intelligence framework that identifies revenue concentration patterns, customer purchasing behavior, and location-level performance insights.

The ultimate objective is to enable data-backed decisions in:

Revenue optimization

Product strategy

Operational efficiency

Store benchmarking

Demand-driven staffing and inventory planning
